@scene intro
title: The Contest
subtitle: A new beginning
on-arrival: inner_zone = 1; loc_thane = 1; loc_rival = 4; loc_shieldmaiden = 6

You step onto the open green before the steading. The wind carries the scent of salt and pine. Warriors and poets alike gather here, drawn by the promise of contest and glory.

Three rings mark the ground — chalk-white against trampled earth. You stand at the near edge of the innermost ring. Across from you, beyond the empty centre, your opponent waits.

Behind you, the Thane watches with arms folded. To your right and behind, a shieldmaiden leans on her spear. Directly beyond your opponent, a rival skald has come to study the exchange.

The story of the Contest has yet to be written.
